Sulfatinib (HMPL-012) is a novel oral small molecule that selectively inhibits vascular endothelial growth factor receptors (VEGFR) 1, 2, and 3 and inhibits FGFR kinase activity has demonstrated potent inhibitory effects on multiple human tumor xenografts.

 This first-in-human study is conducted to assess the maximum tolerated dose (MTD) and recommended dose for phase II ,to evaluate the pharmacokinetics , safety and preliminary anti-tumor activity of HMPL-012 at single doses and multiple doses .

